.TH AUDIOMASON 1 "January 2026" "AudioMason 1.3.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
audiomason \- deterministic audiobook import and tagging tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B audiomason
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
AudioMason is a deterministic audiobook import tool with a staged, resumable workflow.
It separates interactive decision making from non-interactive processing to ensure
safe re-runs and automation.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B import
Import audiobooks from the configured inbox.
.TP
.B verify
Verify an existing audiobook library.
.TP
.B inspect
Read-only inspection of a source without staging or writing output.
.TP
.B cache
Cache maintenance operations.
.SH OPTIONS
Global options include:
.TP
.BR --yes
Run non-interactively using saved or default decisions.
.TP
.BR --dry-run
Do not modify filesystem state.
.TP
.BR --json
Print a machine-readable JSON report at the end of the run.
.TP
.BR --publish " {yes,no,ask}"
Control publish behavior for the current run.
.TP
.BR --wipe-id3
Fully wipe ID3 tags before writing new tags.
.TP
.BR --split-chapters
Split chapterized M4A files into multiple MP3 tracks.
.SH CONFIGURATION
AudioMason reads configuration from config.yaml.
The file config.yaml installed by the package is fully commented and safe by default.
.SH WORKFLOW
AudioMason runs in four phases:
.IP \(bu 2
STAGE \- materialize source into a working area
.IP \(bu 2
PREPARE \- collect and persist all decisions
.IP \(bu 2
PROCESS \- non-interactive output generation
.IP \(bu 2
FINALIZE \- bookkeeping and optional cleanup
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/audiomason/config.yaml
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/audiomason/config.yaml
Authoritative configuration reference.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B AUDIOMASON_DATA_ROOT
Base directory for resolving relative paths.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Error during processing.
